climbs.name: The Matador
climbs.fa: FA: Dustin Hoover, Jim Mercer. November 23, 2012.

content.description: An impressive corner. Death flake deluxe!
content.protection: We did it on a rack to 3" with one 4 and 5 cam each. No bolts or fixed gear.

climbs.name: Enter the Arena
climbs.fa: FA: Dustin Hoover, Jim Mercer. November 23, 2012.

content.description: Good climbing for the rating. The bulge on the white rock offers some good holds for some steep moves. This was our approach pitch for The Bullnose Wall.
content.location: Deep in the south fork of pine creek, below The Bullnose Wall.

climbs.name: Diarrhea Dialect
climbs.fa: FA: Dustin Hoover, Jim Mercer. November 17, 2012.

content.description: A decent corner hidden out of view. Looks harder than it is.
content.protection: Rack to 3". No bolts or fixed gear. Rap off big scrub oak.
content.location: Deep in the south fork of pine creek. Just out of the wash, east facing wall.

climbs.name: The Bullnose Roof
climbs.fa: FA: Dustin Hoover, Jim Mercer November 23, 2012.

content.protection: We did it on a rack to 3" with one 4 and 5 cam each. No bolts or fixed gear.
content.location: If you make it to bullnose wall you wont miss it.

content.description: A wild and remote wall. Approach and descent are fairly complicated and lengthy.
